===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|stamp||}}

# To step quickly and heavily, once or repeatedly.
#:''The toddler screamed and stamped, but still got no candy.''

====Translations====
'''step quickly and heavily'''
{{top}}
*French: [[taper]] du [[pied]]
{{mid}}
*Swedish: [[stampa]]
{{bottom}}

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|stamp||}}

# To move (the [[foot]] or feet) [[quickly]] and [[heavily]], once or [[repeatedly]].
#:''The crowd cheered and '''stamped''' their feet in appreciation.''
# To [[mark]] by [[pressing]] [[quickly]] and [[heavily]].
#:''This machine '''stamps''' the metal cover with a design.''
#:''This machine '''stamps''' the design into the metal cover.''
# To give an [[official]] [[marking]] to, generally by [[impress]]ing or [[imprint]]ing a design or symbol.
#:''The immigration officer '''stamped''' my passport.''
# To apply [[postage stamps]] to.
#:''I forgot to '''stamp''' this letter.''

====Synonyms====

*(''mark by pressing quickly and heavily''): [[emboss]], [[dent]]
*(''give an official marking to''): [[impress]], [[imprint]]

